address\"}],\"stateMutability\":\"view\",\"type\":\"function\"}],\"devdoc\":{\"details\":\"Multi-provider model: the owner can `authorize(address)` peer         providers (e.g. argentum-core's own `GiskardPayments` operator) so         they can anchor their own refs through this contract too. Buyer         agents typically anchor by calling POST https://graphadvocate.com         /agent/score with `anchor=true`; authorized peers can call         markUsed(bytes32) directly from their own wallets.\",\"kind\":\"dev\",\"methods\":{\"markUsed(bytes32)\":{\"params\":{\"ref\":\"the SHA-256 of the JCS-canonicalized preimage per         counterparty-ref-v1.\"}}},\"title\":\"Graph Advocate counterparty-ref anchor registry\",\"version\":1},\"userdoc\":{\"kind\":\"user\",\"methods\":{\"authorize(address)\":{\"notice\":\"Authorize a peer provider to anchor refs through this contract.\"},\"isUsed(bytes32)\":{\"notice\":\"Read-only check \\u2014 verifier reads this AND filters Used events         to confirm anchor attribution.\"},\"markUsed(bytes32)\":{\"notice\":\"Anchor a counterparty-ref. Idempotent \\u2014 reverts on a second         attempt for the same ref so the original anchor block stays         the canonical timestamp.\"},\"revoke(address)\":{\"notice\":\"Revoke a previously-authorized provider. Past anchors remain         valid \\u2014 only future calls from this address will revert.\"}},\"notice\":\"On-chain nullifier registry for the argentum-core counterparty-ref-v1         spec (https://github.com/giskard09/argentum-core/blob/main/docs/spec/counterparty-ref.md).         Interface-compatible with the canonical `GiskardPayments` contract         (`markUsed(bytes32)` / `isUsed(bytes32)`) so verifiers built against         either contract work unchanged.\",\"version\":1}},\"settings\":{\"compilationTarget\":{\"src/RefRegistry.sol\":\"RefRegistry\"},\"evmVersion\":\"cancun\",\"libraries\":{},\"metadata\":{\"bytecodeHash\":\"ipfs\"},\"optimizer\":{\"enabled\":true,\"runs\"